{"source":"LEETCODE","id":"95","title":"Unique Binary Search Trees II","description":"\u003cp\u003eGiven an integer \u003ccode\u003en\u003c/code\u003e, return \u003cem\u003eall the structurally unique \u003cstrong\u003eBST\u0026#39;\u003c/strong\u003es (binary search trees), which has exactly \u003c/em\u003e\u003ccode\u003en\u003c/code\u003e\u003cem\u003e nodes of unique values from\u003c/em\u003e \u003ccode\u003e1\u003c/code\u003e \u003cem\u003eto\u003c/em\u003e \u003ccode\u003en\u003c/code\u003e. Return the answer in \u003cstrong\u003eany order\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong class\u003d\"example\"\u003eExample 1:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cimg alt\u003d\"\" src\u003d\"https://assets.leetcode.com/uploads/2021/01/18/uniquebstn3.jpg\" style\u003d\"width: 600px; height: 148px;\" /\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eInput:\u003c/strong\u003e n \u003d 3\n\u003cstrong\u003eOutput:\u003c/strong\u003e [[1,null,2,null,3],[1,null,3,2],[2,1,3],[3,1,null,null,2],[3,2,null,1]]\n\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong class\u003d\"example\"\u003eExample 2:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eInput:\u003c/strong\u003e n \u003d 1\n\u003cstrong\u003eOutput:\u003c/strong\u003e [[1]]\n\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConstraints:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e1 \u0026lt;\u003d n \u0026lt;\u003d 8\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n","difficulty":"Medium","timeLimit":"","memoryLimit":"","contestProbId":"unique-binary-search-trees-ii","parameterNames":["n"],"testCases":[{"input":"3","expectedOutput":"[[1,null,2,null,3],[1,null,3,2],[2,1,3],[3,1,null,null,2],[3,2,null,1]]"},{"input":"1","expectedOutput":"[[1]]"}]}